221
00:30:00,641 --> 00:30:03,761
<i>Soaring on wind fronts like this</i>

222
00:30:03,841 --> 00:30:08,321
<i>an albatross can travel
hundreds of miles of ocean in a day,</i>

223
00:30:10,001 --> 00:30:12,201
<i>barely beating its wings.</i>

224
00:30:17,641 --> 00:30:20,361
<i>They often spend weeks at sea</i>

225
00:30:20,441 --> 00:30:24,521
<i>searching for prey
without ever returning to land.</i>

226
00:30:36,201 --> 00:30:38,721
<i>Food at last...</i>

227
00:30:38,801 --> 00:30:41,441
<i>A patch of krill close to the surface.</i>

228
00:30:44,321 --> 00:30:46,801
<i>Because the winds are so strong here</i>

229
00:30:46,881 --> 00:30:50,601
<i>albatrosses can afford
the extra weight of waterproofing oils</i>

230
00:30:50,681 --> 00:30:52,281
<i>on their feathers.</i>

231
00:30:54,201 --> 00:30:56,641
<i>They can duck dive
to no more than a meter</i>

232
00:30:56,721 --> 00:31:00,001
<i>so they rely on the churning
